  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Erzberg is on a half board basis.</p>
<p>Each morning you can fuel up for the day at the buffet breakfast with a selection of breads, spreads, charcuterie, yogurts, cereals and pastries. Eggs are made to order. </p>
<p>When it comes to dinnertime a five course evening meal with a choice of menu is served, including regional and international dishes. Once a week you can enjoy a tasty themed buffet. A large selection of wines are available, ask the sommelier for their recommendation of wine pairings. </p>
<p>Christmas and New Year gala dinners included (jacket and tie required)</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p><span>The delightful Hotel Erzberg offers a warm welcome and a high level of comfort and service, and an ideal location in the centre of </span><span><a data-udi="umb://document/754fd3eb2ae94fa89ed0dfc04d2b29b6" href="/{localLink:umb://document/754fd3eb2ae94fa89ed0dfc04d2b29b6}" title="Zurs">Zürs</a>.</span> Caringly run by the friendly Schneider family, it has many personal touches and a great atmosphere.</p>
<h2>Boutique style hotel</h2>
<p>The Charming Erzberg hotel has a lovely feel to it, it is typically Tyrolean and the Schneider family will make you feel welcome from the moment you arrive. The rooms at the Erzberg each have a unique design and furnished to create a luxurious homely experience. They are all equipped with everything needed for a week in the Alps including a TV, Wi-Fi, and bathrobes and slippers for that hint of luxury. For a bit more space, upgrade to the Junior Suite which has a small seating area and lovely views of the mountains.</p>
<h2>Zürs central</h2>
<p>Getting onto the slopes of the Alberg couldn't be easier, the slopes and ski lifts are just snowballs throw away, and the resort centre is a short stroll away. The pretty village of <span><a data-udi="umb://document/754fd3eb2ae94fa89ed0dfc04d2b29b6" href="/{localLink:umb://document/754fd3eb2ae94fa89ed0dfc04d2b29b6}" title="Zurs">Zürs</a> has plenty to keep you occupied when you're not out exploring, including snowshoeing, ice skating and sledding. After a day of snowy adventures be sure to visit the Erzberg Spa with a Finnish sauna, steam bath, infrared cabin and a relaxation area - massages are also available for a local fee.</span></p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
